page.title: 04CUB DISTRICT CAMP BURWELL.
page.content: This year's annual camp was held at {Margaret Field}in Burwell.People came by car from places like Newmarket, Snailwell, Soham, Chippenham,Bottisham and Swaffham Prior,as well as Burwell. The{53 Cubs}had to be{seconders or {sixers.}There were also 21 leaders and The District Commissioner.20 tents were used and a dining marquee.The adults did most of the cooking.There was a tuck-shop too. Cubs made things like special signs with sticks.They lit fires and cooked carrots,roast potatoes and pork chops. They went on hikes.A super-stars competition was also held.All the activities had points for{The Antler {award.}The Burwell group were runners- up for that{best pack prize}but won the quiz.
